Despite the place having great food, service is an important part of a restaurant experience. Extremely rude service! The blonde server basically threw us the dish and handed in the check early.

The staff were friendly and the food was delicious and fresh. For the starters we ordered The Little Choc Classic Parfait. The coconut based yogurt was light, the granola tasted homemade, and the banana was the perfect ripeness. We requested for the caramel on the side and it wasn't overly sweet. It tasted unique in a good way. I requested to have the unused portion to take home because it was just so good. Exceptional dessert that tasted super fresh and healthy.  I ordered the Burrito crepe and my SO ordered Jacked up. They're both savory crepes but very different flavors.  The burrito had a hint of spiciness and the cashew cheese flavor really stood out. The coconut bacon added a nice crunch. I'm amazed it's vegan. I can believe it if someone had told me it's vegetarian, but it's mind blowing that it's vegan.  I had a few bites of the Jacked up and it's delicious. If you prefer more of a BBQ flavor, it might be more up you alley. I prefer a creamier and denser food so the burrito outshines the jacked up for me.  For our drinks we ordered a pot of unlimited Headache Be Gone tea. They use actual tea leaves, flowers, herbs, and plants. I was brought up drinking tea (not the store bought teabags kind) and I wasn't expecting such good tea. There's even a cute hourglass that indicates 1, 3, and 5 minutes. I recommend letting it soak for at least 5 minutes to bring out the flavor if you prefer a strong flavor.  Will be back. I hope they are able to stay open because it's a great cute delicious vegan spot.
The place is beautiful and the food  delicious! Had a wonderful vegan breakfast and fresh orange juice.

The preparation has been super quick whenever I've ordered delivery during the pandemic and it really feels like healing food. Can't wait to go in person soon.

So let me start by just saying that the food here is DELICIOUS.  I’m trying to be vegan for 2 weeks and my mom found this place. She was not expecting to like anything vegan whatsoever but she loved it and would go back (and she is absolutely not vegan). I ordered food to pick up. My only reasons/criticisms for taking off 1 star are: 1. The prices on the google maps menu are different than what their actual prices are right now. The items are about $4 more than listed on google maps. My total was way more than I expected. Still ok, but I’d recommend updating the app so customers have the right expectation to what they will pay when they arrive/pickup. 2. Some items in my pickup order were incorrect. For example, one crepe I ordered strawberry jam and got fresh strawberries instead; I ordered coconut bacon on one and got coconut flakes instead. Regardless, they were still delicious. 3. It took about 45min to cook. I was quoted 30, kind of long either way but worth the wait. Again, the food was delicious and I would go back whether I end up sticking with veganism or not.

Long overdue review. I don't even know how the food is because I gave up and left. I stopped in during my lunch break. There were at least five people "working" at the main counter. I tried look at the menu board but was shooed upstairs and told someone would be with me. And then I waited. And waited. And waited. At this point I just felt awkward and embarrassed because I was by myself, the only Black customer and so obviously being ignored.  The restaurant was hardly full and I didn't know if the staff was just bad or if I was being ignored because I was Black. Either way, it was mortifying. After about twenty minutes I went back downstairs and saw all of them just chatting and laughing, doing absolutely nothing. I asked them how long they were going to make me wait and they finally stopped talking but I just left at that point.  What a ridiculous restaurant.

I went there for a single dinner and it was great. The staff was super friendly and helpful. The food was amazing! It's an art to cook and bake vegan and gluten-free food that tastes even better than non-vegan food. I had a very delicious crepe with mushrooms, spinach and walnuts and cashew-based cheese (so tasty) at the side. It was so good, if I wouldn't have been full after one I would have loved to try all the other savory crepes too. I also had a crunchy-soft scone with coconutmilk-based clotted cream and homemade raspberry jam. Really, this vegan restaurant (for breakfast, lunch, afternoon tea and dinner) is a must-visit for people who appreciate very tasty, qualitative animal-free and gluten-free food!
My second time here and it was even better than the first. I love bbq jackfruit and they just so happened to have a bbq jackfruit crepe.
The tea was great and the crepe was surperb .. definitely will be back!

Delicious, fun, and has multiple items to try! The most difficult decisions you’ll need to make is what you want to order... staff are friendly and the location is cute but roomy. I would highly suggest the gluten free crepes!  Go go go!
First of all the service is amazing. Friendly warm and efficient! Then the place is cozy and cute! The açaí bowl I took for breakfast was just perfect :-) Im happy I discovered this place💃🏻
I love whoever invented this place
All vegan and gluten free crepes! The staff was all so nice and attentive. The tea is amazing as well, perfect place to post up and read/get work done.
Great crepes and smoothies, even if you're not vegan you won't miss a thing!
Good coffee
Great lemonade with agave
Delicious spiced hot cocoa, warm chocolate chip cookies and chocolate mud cake!
Great food! Friendly staff! Come with some time though, orders take a while.
These are not real creepes! The smoothie was delicious though.

Good menu and raw options! I’ll be back to try the crepes someday. A bit overpriced. My green smoothie was 300 ml and I think was too much for the size and what it had. But understand in NY things are more and more expensive..! I liked the B12 raw energy ball concept.
The crepes are great

I loved the coconut bacon, I took two stars off because of the flies, fruit flies, and coffee that tasted burnt. They really need to get with the program and provide Oat milk, the creamers they provide for the coffee all separate and leave the coffee with a weird texture. My friend and I split 2 crepes.  One sweet with nutella, bananas, and almonds, it was amazing! The other crepe was a savory one called “the burrito” or something like that. I highly recommend splitting a savory and sweet with a friend. Just getting one whole sweet one might be too much sweetness in one sitting. Gluten free and vegan, so just about anyone can eat here and be happy.

Great environment for hanging out or working. Is really chill and nicely decorated. Im not vegan but I enjoy vegan food a lot. In my case unfortunately the food was not pleasant for my stomach so I did not enjoyed. Maybe was that specific plate, or something not well cooked. Besides that, is a nice place.

I love this spot! It is such an adorable little cafe with an upstairs that has tables next to the window.  I couldn't believe it was all vegan and gluten free it was so hearty and flavorful! They also serve unique mimosas and coffees!

Crepe café that knows how to build a recipe. I got a savory mushroom crepe, and it was amazing. My friends, who are not vegan, said that it was the best crepe they ever had. Service was amazing and attentive. Even after we paid, we chatted for another 10 mins at the table, and she still came through and refilled our beverages. I do not live near Brooklyn, but I would recommend this spot to anyone traveling to the area, whether they are vegan or not.
Stop by for delicious vegan crepes and refreshing teas. Small place with lots of good vibes.

This place is organic, vegan, Gluten Free, and still manages to have fantastic pastries, baked goods, sweet and savory crepes, and 5,000 tea options. Their beer and wine is BOGO during weekday happy hour. They even make their own wellness tea blends, aka APOTHECARY.  Specials happening often.  a hidden GEM! Also...VEG SPEED DATING!
Delicious :) I came here with my boyfriend and we loved it.

So cute! They have a great tea selection and give you an hourglass sand timer to steep your tea appropriately. The decor is colorful, eclectic and quaint and the food is healthy and fresh. I love sitting on the second floor by the window and looking out onto the busy street. #yummy #vegetarianfriendly #eclectic #colorful
Honestly, I didn't think I liked crepes... now I know I only like amazing crepes. This is a great spots for vegans and vegetarians. The staff were super helpful and friendly too.
Crepes that are way more than you expect!
Good vegan crepes and variety. Within walking distance of subways.
great
Love this place!
Love their burrito crepe, yum!
Delicious crepes. Savory and sweet, what a treat.

Delicious vegan AND gluten free crepes! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, the portions served pleasent, and the staff incredibly friendly. I'm vegan and I have a gluten free friend and it's not typically easy to find a restaurant that works for both of us. Loved it here, and I can't wait to become a frequent patron.
Cute spot for breakfast. Food wasn’t that tasty but the atmosphere was nice and the service was good
Amaaaazing crepes!

(Translated by Google) We went there for brunch on a Saturday morning and waited 1 hour for our pancakes to arrive and on top of that they were cold. You should know that in addition to the room there is the bar and take-away sales which are very numerous and which come before the room. I do not recommend this place.  (Original) Nous y sommes allés pour un brunch un samedi matin et nous avons attendu 1 heure que nos crêpes arrivent et en plus elles étaient froides. Il faut savoir qu'en plus de la salle il y a le bar et les ventes à emporter qui sont très nombreuses et qui passent avant la salle. Je ne recommande pas cet endroit.

A wonderful selection of teas and tisanes with unbelievably delicious vegan crepes! The space is bright and cheerful, but the kitchen is very small so if you come for weekend brunch, expect a fairly significant wait for your food but know that the wait is 100% worth it!

Prices were very unreasonable. 15$ for a coffee, orange juice, and a cookie. That would be fine if it was satisfying or at a higher quality, but coffee was terrible, the orange juice was not freshly squeezed, and the cookie was overly sweet. On top of this, understaffed and service was frustratingly slow (given the backlog). Would never step foot in this cafe again.
Delicious food. The pizza crepe is the best.
Can’t wait to go back. Have the affogato. Nothing like quality coffee and ice cream.
Cute place...  Great food!
auper good blck coffee
My favorite crepe place! They never disappoint and I am always so satisfied afterwards :)

Visited the Little Choc Apothecary before noon and had a delicious and filling vegan crêpe! I ordered the one with jackfruit, kale and red peppers. While it‘s a bit more pricey than I intended to spend (15$ for the crepe) it was such an amazing experience to eat in this restaurant! The staff is very welcoming, helpful and I also felt comfortable eating on my own. A big plus is, that everything they serve is glutenfree!

I came here with a friend who highly recommended this place, and we we ended up having the most ridiculous experience. We ordered crepes and we waited for the crepes to come for 1 hr. 1 HOUR. Finally we asked a waiter what was keeping the food since it was obviously not busy, and he came back and told us that our waiter had given our crepes to another person. Meanwhile she was sitting in the corner on her break not even paying attention to us. We couldn't even believe the horrible service and we left very upset. Fortunately we were able to find a place around the corner where the staff was very attentive. I will definitely not come back again.
Delicious pancakes (tried pizza and burrito) & pleasant atmosphere :-)
Waited 45 min for my tea, 1 hour for my food. No compensation or even an excuse. Never coming back

Crepes are amazing. Would recommen Garden of Eatin, Room for Shroom and the Choc Butter (newtella) and banana crepes. I am not a vegan but thoroughly enjoyed this place. The chai lattes here are not very tasty tho :(
THIS PLACE IS GOOD! If you’re vegan you’ll be very happy. Prefer the sweet crepes over savory but recommend trying BOTH 🙌🏾🙌🏾

Little Choc is a great spot — I live in the neighborhood, so I’ve a bunch of times.  There are so many wonderful food and drink options! I love the burrito and pizza crepes, the golden smoothie, the *earl grey* cookies, and the lattes with a mix of (homemade!) almond and coconut milks!!  Several of my immediate family members are vegetarian or vegan, so I’ve taken them to Little Choc, and they loved having so many options and the food.  Oh, and the staff are awesome, in my experience — friendly, attentive, and helpful. And the upstairs area is really lovely!

Go, go, go out of your way if you have to to visit the Little Choc Apothecary. Their all-vegan menu is to die for (try the homemade nutella, seriously) and the staff is genuinely friendly and upbeat. Great place to warm up on a chilly day too and sip a cup of deliciously herbal tea served in antique-ware.
Best crepes in the world!

The acai bowl was very poorly made. Some frozen fruit that were blended were still in huge chunks difficult to eat. It was just granola and chunks of frozen blant fruit.  For two of those and a smoothie was more than 50$ it was our first time visiting that place definitely no worth another trip.
Nice spot for tea, chats with friends or a cute date night.
Awesome food and staff. A cool place to hang, catch up and knosh
Amazing crêpes! Light, fresh, filling. Warm hug from the inside.

Highly enjoyed this gem in the city! Their vegan chocolate banana crepe is something that I would definitely order again. Their tea was tasty and they had an array of different flavours to cater to anyone and their different palettes. The service was friendly and ambiance seemed very relaxed on the day we came since it wasn't busy. Would come back and try other items on the menu.
goog coffee.

I was looking for a local coffee place while I was walking in Market St, and this place showed it. It is hidden, but thanks to the phone GPS I did not get lost. I ordered their filtered/distilled coffee. It unique, and has a bold sweet taste. I wish this place can open another place to where I live!
Amazing selection of vegan crepes. Service was a little slow but it was quite busy.
Stopped for a quick bite. I enjoyed the burrito- black beans, avocado, coconut bacon and their special hot sauce. A lot of flavor and hit the spot!
ITS EXTREMELY SLOW. Waitresses are slow, food is slow, delivery is slow. If you’re positive that you’ll live till you’re 100 years old, this is the perfect place to eat.
2017 Very cozy....comfy and relax....with my fav crepe...health wheat....a little dry...OK

Sadly my trip to this restaurant was a disaster. First of all, the air was so bad, I could barely breathe. Then, the cappuccino didn’t taste like anything that had ever been served to me as cappuccino. And after eating the crêpes, I felt sick all afternoon - probably too much fat. I‘m sorry, but I wouldn‘t recommend.
The acai bowls, juices,  smoothies,  and coffee were all delicious. The gold cold ninja juice was particularly amazing.
Awesome spot. Great for vegans. Delicious. Chill. Quirky. Highlight of our trip.

Fantastic Vegan & Gluten free crepes. The 'burrito' is a perfect blend of tradition & plant based innovation. As a huge fan of vegetarian and vegan restaurants I've tried mushroom and spinach in every combination possible. The 'room for mushroom' crepe was an amazing twist on this classic combo! Definitely will be back as I only got to try one of their 40+ amazing tea options!

I went here for a late-ish brunch. We were able to get a seat right away and the upstairs was empty except for two tables. The space filled up quickly though and all tables were occupied when we left.  The crepes were nice - I wouldn't say exceptional but good. The portion sizes were great though. We were considering getting two savoury crepes and one sweet to share between both of us. Luckily we only got two savoury ones as we were struggling to finish even these.  Even the drinks were big. I got a coffee which came in a huge mason jar!
Food was ok and the place was nice The service was horrible Never ever in my life happened to me to wait 1 hour and 45 min for a crepe Only 4 tables so no excuse
Pizza Crepe and Burrito crepe were my 1st and so delicious. Very filling! FOH person was very congenial and warm, BOH seemed like they wanted to be invisible. Small space, I get it.

Second time back after my initial visit which made me want to return enough times to try everything on the menu! So filling, so wholesome, great music, great vibe! Brooklyn is quite a trek for me but it's my go-to whenever I have something in Williamsburg :)
My favourite place everrr. Healthy and clearing all the matters.
Cutest spot ever! Great vibes!! Crepes are amazing!! Apple pie mimosa also amazing!!
Great little place, amazing food and very nice, helpful staff. A must visit for vegans or crepe fans!!!
Although it took forever to be seated, even though we had a reservation... the food was tasty and the service was good. Definitely recommend for a nice snack.
Greatest vegan crepes ever 😍
Lovely vegan bake shop, creperie, and tea room. Loved the tea pots.

I've been here twice. I liked the burrito crepe and one of their shakes. Can't remember what it was called, but it's the only green shake with apples in it. It's earthy and chill atmosphere. Their syrup and sauces are homemade. Their crepe is thick, almost like a pancake. Probably the only vegan creperie around. Lunch time is a good time to go, not very many people. A good place to go when you want something sweet and filing and vegan.
Great vegan menu
Excellent Vegan Pancakes, both savory and sweet . Whole place offers one of the best vegan dishes ever tried.
Great coffee
Food is amazing. Service is perfect. Ambiance is on point. God, I’m so full right now. I ate too many crepes!!!
My first question is always "what's the scone of the day?" Like it matters! They are all delicious and I'm taking home one regardless. Don't forget the clotted cream and jam!

The crepes were tasty, nothing exceptional though. I loved the upstairs space and the decor but the staff were a bit robotic and very intent on upselling. We got caught out, I suppose some would say that the waitress was a good salesperson but what annoyed me was that she offered us almond and coconut milk for our hot drinks without telling us that they would cost more. We found it on the pricey side too.
Great vegan crepes and a huge assortment of teas.
This little place has some amazing teas for all occasions!

Sorry, gluten free crepes just don't taste good. Maybe I got the wrong order (garden of eden and a scone) but I couldn't finish it! So expensive too. But happy it's organic and the interior was so quaint!!

Ate deliciouse savoury crepes in the evening defenitially coming back for brunch to try their sweet options. Payed 1$ more for cashew cheese which was not worth the 1$ portion and our pancakes took pretty much time since the people around us got their crepes earlier than us, while we got in before them. Flavours were great!
